# Gitleaks fingerprint-based ignores.
#
# Fingerprints have the form `<file>:<rule-id>:<line>` — they pin to the
# exact (path, rule, line) triple of a single finding, so muting one false
# positive doesn't silently mute a real leak in the same file.
#
# Get a fingerprint by running locally:
#
#     gitleaks git -v --redact
#
# and copying the `Fingerprint:` line of the finding you want to ignore.
#
# Prefer per-line `# gitleaks:allow` markers over fingerprints when the
# false positive is on a specific line you control — the marker is right
# next to the value, so a future reader sees why it's allowed without
# having to cross-reference this file. Fingerprints are best for findings
# in generated files / docs where adding inline markers would be awkward.
